						<div class="postbody">The goal is to get a tone equal to the frequency of E-3. <br /><br />According to the <a href="http://famitracker.com/wiki/index.php?title=Basic_frequency_register_table" class="postlink">famitracker wiki</a>, e3 uses a value of $152 for its frequency. According to the formula on the same page, (1789772.727 / 16) / (Frequency register + 1),  that'd be a frequency of ~726.368, which according to my synthesizer and <a href="https://pages.mtu.edu/~suits/notefreqs.html" class="postlink">this</a> chart is almost an F#. So i know it ought to be wrong already, but i used audacity to generate a duty of that frequency. When i import the duty, loop it, and play it, it plays back as an &quot;almost B&quot; with the frequency set to &quot;15&quot;. <br /><br />What am i doing wrong here? I must've misunderstood something fundamental.</div>

					
