				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">FrankenGraphics wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">then snip out one perfect duty, export it as .wav, and import into famitracker. Even with the new frequency, it yields a B.<br /><br />If i add several duties in a string (which seems a little wasteful?), i do get the intended frequency but with a looping stutter.</div><br />Looping is tricky with DPCM because the length register requires all waves to be 128 * n + 8 samples long. Practically, you need to use a 136-sample loop (which gives the key of B major), a 264-sample loop (which requires tuning everything else up 50 cents or a quarter tone), or an unlooped wave with several periods (which is what Sunsoft games do).<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">FrankenGraphics wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">It also looks more lite a triform than a square in the oscilloscope view and sounds the part.</div><br />That's slope overload, one of the hard-to-avoid characteristics of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Delta_modulation" class="postlink">delta modulation</a>.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

