					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">A few years ago I sat down and made DPCM triangle waves for every integer divisor (edit: except divisors that are multiples of 16. Those can't be represented, because there are no integers <em>m, n</em> just that <em>2·m=16·n+1</em> ). They're not too big, and they help compensate for the DPCM's stupid tuning table.<br /><br /><!-- l --><a class="postlink-local" href="https://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=154032#p154032">viewtopic.php?p=154032#p154032</a><!-- l --></div>

